occurs in the absence of Fe catalystparticles, and that the concentration of\ndifferent carbon species (e.g. carbon dioxide and ethylene) is sensitive to the\nreactor tube type. These finding open new avenues for controlled synthesis of\nCNT fibers by decoupling precursor decomposition from CNT extrusion at the\ncatalyst particle.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 19 Nov 2020 22:44:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-11-23"}
